I haven’t seen enough of attention being given to the Yemen Crisis on here, at least not in depth. Most people don’t know that it was only recently in the 90’s that Yemen’s Shia-Majority North and Sunni-majority South combined into 1 country (thus the colors of the flag). This civil war began with the “Houthi” (A Zaidi Shia Group) rebellion against the oppresive government, which lead to the death of President Saleh in 2017. The UAE and KSA and even the USA have been supporting the Yemeni Government in their war against the Houthi rebels, who have also caused death and destruction and most would say they no longer fight for a noble cause. Now the whole region is just a dumpster fire which cannot be put out has been fueled even more by the 2019 Cholera Outbreak and Covid-19 as well. Yemen is already a very water-poor country, and hundreds of thousands of displaced families don’t have access to clean water or the means to protect themselves from diseases. UNICEF estimates that a child dies every ten minutes in Yemen of preventable diseases; that is about 50,000 and growing each year. There has been an unprecedented rate of civilian casualties in this war, and the Shias especially, continue to be tormented mentally and physically. The refugees are having a particularly hard time escaping to safety with Covid travel restrictions, and while a cease-fire was attempted, it did not stick. 

Please read more about this crisis at the link in my bio, and help raise awareness. If you are able to donate to relief funds, now is the time, if not, donate your time to learning more about what is happening to our fellow humans (and fellow Muslims). 

